Today we will make a special dish from Punjab cuisine .i.e. methi matar malai.

00:00:13.983 --> 00:00:21.175
This dish is very rich in taste and you will surely like eating it.

00:00:21.792 --> 00:00:27.903
Let's see what all ingredients are required for making methi malai matar.

00:00:28.601 --> 00:00:44.590
Methi - 250 grams
Remove stalk and separate leaves. Rinse with water twice and strain excess water with help of a sieve.

00:00:45.404 --> 00:00:47.928
Green peas - ½ cup (frozen)

00:00:48.359 --> 00:01:02.394
Fine paste - 3 tomatoes, 1 green chilly, 1 inch ginger piece and 10-12 cashew nuts

00:01:03.303 --> 00:01:09.616
Cream - ½ cup (can also use fresh homemade malai)

00:01:10.455 --> 00:01:12.066
Oil - 2 tbsp

00:01:12.592 --> 00:01:14.814
Coriander powder - 1 tsp

00:01:15.174 --> 00:01:20.619
Salt - more then ½ tsp or as per taste

00:01:21.220 --> 00:01:25.149
Red chilly powder - ¼ tsp

00:01:25.763 --> 00:01:37.113
Whole garam masala - ½ inch cinnamon stick, 2 brown cardamom, 2 cloves and 5-6 black pepper

00:01:37.585 --> 00:01:43.787
Instead of all these you can also use ¼ tsp garam masala powder.

00:01:52.401 --> 00:01:53.592
Asafoetida - 1 pinch

00:01:54.325 --> 00:01:56.126
Cumin seeds - ½ tsp

00:01:56.630 --> 00:01:58.956
Sugar - ½ tsp

00:02:00.825 --> 00:02:07.337
Firstly chop methi leaves for making the Sabzi.

00:02:07.943 --> 00:02:17.109
Make a bunch of leaves in your hands like this and chop them finely with help of a chopping blade.

00:02:39.069 --> 00:02:45.172
Take methi leaves and peas in any utensil and place on flame for boiling.

00:02:45.673 --> 00:02:50.443
Add ½ cup in utensil and let it boil.

00:02:56.015 --> 00:03:02.781
Meanwhile make masala for Sabzi.

00:03:07.084 --> 00:03:08.481
Add oil in the pan.

00:03:13.307 --> 00:03:23.904
When water starts boiling add peas and methi leaves into it.

00:03:29.989 --> 00:03:35.795
Cover the utensil and cook for 5 minutes.

00:03:44.116 --> 00:04:09.623
When oil gets hot add asafoetida, cumin seeds, coriander powder and paste of tomato-green chilly-ginger and cashew nuts.

00:04:10.072 --> 00:04:19.189
Sauté it until oil starts floating on the surface.

00:04:20.623 --> 00:04:32.139
Also add red chilly powder and coarsely ground garam masala.

00:04:33.629 --> 00:04:37.995
Stir after every 1-2 minutes.

00:04:43.290 --> 00:04:48.806
Masala is now ready.

00:05:01.842 --> 00:05:05.818
Methi leaves and peas are also ready now.

00:05:08.429 --> 00:05:23.401
Now add cream, sugar and salt in the masala and mix well.

00:05:23.769 --> 00:05:30.129
If you prefer not adding sugar in the masala then avoid using it.

00:05:36.847 --> 00:05:45.638
If you like eating bitter taste of methi then; add it directly in the masala along with water.

00:05:50.161 --> 00:06:03.259
If you don't like eating its bitter taste then strain the water and then add in the masala.

00:06:05.299 --> 00:06:14.009
Add water in gravy as per your preference or add ½ cup water.

00:06:18.527 --> 00:06:29.350
Cover the pan and cook for 2-3 minutes so that all spices get absorbed in the methi and peas.

00:06:39.970 --> 00:06:45.446
Methi matar malai is ready; take it out in a bowl.

00:06:51.491 --> 00:06:57.792
Mouth watering methi matar malai with rich gravy is ready.

00:06:58.872 --> 00:07:04.729
Make this dish for any special occasion or party.

00:07:05.147 --> 00:07:12.237
Serve with chapatti, naan, parantha or rice.

